To build kint, you need LLVM 3.1 or later, and Clang.  One option is
to install recent versions of LLVM and Clang from Ubuntu 12.10 (earlier
versions of Ubuntu have older versions of LLVM that are not compatible
with kint):

	$ apt-get install llvm-dev clang

Another option is to build the latest LLVM & Clang, as detailed at:

	http://clang.llvm.org/get_started.html

We use the following parameters to LLVM's configure:

	--enable-optimized --enable-targets=host --enable-bindings=none --enable-shared --enable-debug-symbols

Then build kint:

	$ autoreconf -fvi
	$ mkdir build
	$ ( cd build && ../configure )
	$ ( cd build && make )
